WorldStage Newsonline– Nigeria’s Senate on Wednesday received a request from President Muhammadu Buhari to confirm the nomination of Joe Aniku Michael Ohiani as substantive Director-General/CEO for the Infrastructure Concession Regulatory Commission (ICRC). The Senate also received a formal request to confirm the nomination of Umar Yahaya as Co-Chairman of the Governing Council of Unclaimed Funds Trust Funds. The request for ICRC was contained in a letter dated 6th June, 2022. The President’s letter was read at the commencement of plenary proceedings by the Senate President, Ahmad Lawan. According to Buhari, the confirmation request was in accordance with the provision of Section 22(1)(a) of the Infrastructure Concession Regulatory Commission (Establishment) Act, 2005. The request for Umar Yahaya was contained in a letter dated 3rd June, 2022. President Buhari, in the letter, explained that his request was made pursuant to Section 77(5) of the Finance Act 2020.